# Coordinated updates (Female Contemporary Artist 1)

When you change one area, finish the job: update **all** artifacts that depend on it, then run **targeted** commands before handing off.

## `data.js` (content)

| Change | Also update / do |
|--------|------------------|
| New or changed artist `image` | `docs/IMAGE_CREDITS.md` entry for that file; run `npm run check:images` |
| New artist fields used by Ask (e.g. keywords, `wikipediaTitle`) | Sanity: Ask still resolves; extend `test/artist-retrieval.test.mjs` if scoring/flatten rules change |
| New/changed `quiz` (must be **exactly 5** per bank) | `e2e/quiz-flow.spec.ts` / `e2e/quiz-data-invariant.spec.ts` if assumptions break; topic/series copy if UI depends on it |
| New series/topic or “coming soon” behavior | Relevant `e2e/*.spec.ts` (e.g. `series-coming-soon`, topic counts) |

## `app.js` / `index.html` / `style.css` (UI & flow)

| Change | Also update / do |
|--------|------------------|
| New screen, renamed screen, or navigation | Only `navigate()` / `renderScreen()` for visibility; wire `index.html` section if needed; styles in `style.css`; e2e if user paths change |
| Favorites, quiz UI, landing CTAs | Matching `e2e/*.spec.ts` |

## `lib/artist-retrieval.js`

| Change | Also update / do |
|--------|------------------|
| Scoring, flattening, exports | `test/artist-retrieval.test.mjs`; if Ask prompt/context uses new fields, smoke `api/ask.js` |

## `api/ask.js`

| Change | Also update / do |
|--------|------------------|
| Request/response shape, env vars, model behavior | `test/api-ask.test.mjs`; `env.example` if new env; README/Ask troubleshooting only if user-facing behavior changes |

## Before finishing a task

1. Run `npm test` after non-trivial edits (or at minimum the slice you touched: `npx playwright test path/to/spec.ts`, `npm run test:unit`, `npm run check:images` as applicable).
2. If `CLAUDE.md` documents behavior you changed, align that file in the same change set.

Do not stop after a single file when the checklist above still has unchecked items for your edit.
